numPrimacy: Number of primacy images to be taken from the neutral folder
numRecency: Number of recency images to be taken from the neutral folder
numTrainStimFromEachValence: The number of stimulus to be taken per valence. half with be famil and half will be foils. these will then be split into those that will be shown at test 1 and test 2 respectivly
trainBetweenStimDuration: Time between images after subject has ans all Qs
testBetweenStimDuration: time between images at test after the confidence selection
encodingInstructionBlurb: Instruction Text that displays below images at start of encoding
trainBlurb: text that displays at start of training
test1InitBlurb: text that displays at start of test 1
test2InitBlurb: text that displays at start of test 2
acceptableTestAns: The possible answers that subjects can enter at test

testInstructBlurb:
PRESENT

1 = for high confidence - you are certain

2 = average confidence - you are moderately sure

3 = low confidence - you are not sure but you think it was present

NOT PRESENT

7 = high confidence - you are certain

8 = average confidence - you are moderately sure

9 = low confidence - you are not sure but you think it was NOT there
